{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I think I ought to record it for posterity that it is a statistical fact that the Austrian [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people represented 8% of the German army, but over 50% of the war criminals.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Let it remain at that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now, the-- so therefore, what I remember is that, whilst you could get all sorts of fruit and foodstuffs in Hungary, there was a shortage.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You couldn't get bananas, coconuts, [LAUGHS] and [LAUGHS] maybe one other product.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know, the stupid things which one remembers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I remember that my father always gave instructions to his tenant, whenever you go up to Vienna, you bring back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This is already after the Anschluss.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Nevertheless, what we-- there was apparently somehow organized that the Jews who were ostracized in, in, in, in Austria-- the people didn't dare to say good morning to them or, or, or knock on their doors-- and stayed till the-- 1941, '42, or '40, '41, '42, were allowed to receive what they called [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "These were like a registered envelope in which you were allowed to put in a hundred grams-- in other words, 10 decagrams.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Or if you like to convert it into pounds, it's less than a quarter of a pound of foodstuff, mainly meat, either raw or cooked, which was within two hours in Vienna and probably delivered the same day or the next day to various addresses.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I remember every week, we kept on addressing dozens and dozens of, of, of envelopes, of these little package envelopes, and sending food up to the people who we didn't even know.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We just got lists.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Probably they individually or the community supplied it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That is what I remember very clearly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We know that eventually all of them got deported.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
